I'm getting a different error as the original poster, but with the same cause - when I set num_epochs equal in tf.contrib.slim.parallel_reader.parallel_read to anything other than None, my FIFOQueues crash:

OutOfRangeError (see above for traceback): FIFOQueue '_1_batch_examples_using_buckets/bucket_by_sequence_length/bucket/top_queue' is closed and has insufficient elements (requested 1, current size 0)

Does this error have the same root cause as the tensorflow.python.framework.errors_impl.FailedPreconditionError? I would guess not. If so, does anyone know what might be causing this error?

body:
I'm getting a different error as the original poster, but with the same cause - when I set num_epochs equal in `tf.contrib.slim.parallel_reader.parallel_read` to anything other than `None`, my `FIFOQueues` crash:

`OutOfRangeError (see above for traceback): FIFOQueue '_1_batch_examples_using_buckets/bucket_by_sequence_length/bucket/top_queue' is closed and has insufficient elements (requested 1, current size 0)`

Does this error have the same root cause as the `tensorflow.python.framework.errors_impl.FailedPreconditionError`? I would guess not. If so, does anyone know what might be causing this error?
